  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Administrator (Sales Support)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Responsibilities</strong></p><p>Engineering Sales Support</p><ul><li><p>Handle and respond to customer enquiries related to Engineering Sales.</p></li><li><p>Monitor and ensure all customer enquiries are attended to and resolved promptly.</p></li><li><p>Prepare, process, and follow up on sales quotations.</p></li><li><p>Review completed jobs and submit documentation for invoicing.</p></li><li><p>Liaise with customers on Goods Receipt (GR) status for customer portal submissions.</p></li><li><p>Coordinate with the Field Service Department on pending Purchase Requisition (PR) and Purchase Order (PO) matters.</p></li></ul><p>Contract Sales Support</p><ul><li><p>Handle customer enquiries related to Contract Sales.</p></li><li><p>Monitor and ensure timely follow-up and resolution of customer enquiries.</p></li><li><p>Process billings for Maintenance Contracts and coordinate with Finance on billing-related matters.</p></li><li><p>Submit Bills of Quantity (BQ) and follow up with customers on PO and GR status.</p></li><li><p>Process billings for Permit-To-Operate (PTO) Contracts and coordinate with Finance on billing-related issues.</p></li></ul><p>General Support</p><ul><li><p>Provide support for insurance-related matters.</p></li><li><p>Coordinate and manage annual customer surveys.</p></li><li><p>Perform general administrative duties, including filing, documentation, and stationery management.</p></li><li><p>Coordinate meetings and prepare meeting minutes.</p></li><li><p>Coordinate with Event PIC on CSR and company activities.</p></li><li><p>Perform any other tasks or special assignments as directed by the Head of Department to support sales operations.</p></li><li></li></ul><p><strong>Job Requirements</strong></p><ul><li><p>Diploma / Advanced / Higher / Graduate qualification in Business Administration or related fields.</p></li><li><p>Minimum 5 years of relevant experience in business administration or sales support.</p></li><li><p>Experience in the same industry is an advantage.</p></li><li><p>Good working knowledge of CRM systems, SAP, and Microsoft Office.</p></li><li><p>Strong interpersonal and communication skills; able to work effectively with all levels of staff.</p></li><li><p>Able to commence work at short notice.</p></li></ul>",
